5. What is Business Process Flow(BPF)?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ A Business Process Flow (BPF) is a visual and guided workflow that helps users to follow a set of predefined steps to complete a business process.
ğŸ‘‰ It standardizes data entry, enforces business rules, and ensures consistency across teams by guiding users through different stages of a process.

âœ… In my previous project, I used Business Process Flow (BPF) in a model-driven app to streamline the Customer Onboarding process. 
âœ… The business needed a standardized, step-by-step guide for sales representatives to follow, ensuring no critical step was missed.
ğŸ”¹ I created a BPF with stages like Lead Qualification â†’ Account Setup â†’ Document Collection â†’ Final Approval.
ğŸ”¹ At each stage, I added mandatory fields (steps) like Email, Company Name, Document Upload.
ğŸ”¹ I implemented branching logic, so if any document was missing, the user couldnâ€™t proceed.
ğŸ”¹ I also configured role-based access, so only managers could approve at the final stage.

